discourse_list.title: Sending not correct crypto on ERC20 contract

content.content: Hi . I send DAI from my Binance account to waves.exchange contract when they not support DAI deposits. It was USDT address I believe. It happens almost 3 years ago and since then I am talking with C.S. of waves.exchange and they keep on telling be they are working on that. The funds is visible on the blockchain. The contract is definitely maker.dao Is there any other options to get my money back? I made mistake, and I told them that. But the money not went into nimbo. They are in their wallet. What else can I do? Please help.
Thanks for the massage but that really is up to waves exchange if you sent it there. Sorry to hear that
